<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO JEFF WINKLER</font><br>
<tt>Wed Feb 12 17:09:37 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To jeffert Winkler<br><br>
I in no way stated that the protestors caused us to lose the war. Nor do I accept the idea the protestors ended the war sooner. Because neither is a fact based in reality. i get tired of hearing the self righteous demeanor of the protestors claiming to have been the cuase of the end of the war.<br><br>
They did not. The politics of the war ran its course andd died an unrighteous death and only served to divide this nation. To bad you can't see that.<br><br>
To Doc Del<br><br>
Thanks for defending me. My bitterness towards the protestors may some day come to an end.<br><br>
To JJ <br><br>
It's cool guy. Even when I went to group meetings angers flared. Someday everyone will get a gripo and accept responsibility for their actions and stop blaming everyone else. Hang in there and fight back when attacted.<br><br>
I try to keep cool but as you can see I get angry when idiots see something else in my words that was not there.<br><br>
As for the history lesson and the question as to why the protestors only saw the bad guys were the American GI. My thoughts on this are:<br><br>
We vets were readily at hand. We were the face of which blame could be fixed upon. We were the people that could be attacted and abused because we were the ones doing the killing. It does not matter that the Kmer Rouge killed millions between 1965 and 1995. Yeah, Their killing has continued to this decade. But they are not aproachable. Thay are half a world away. We vets are here now as we were then. It has always been easier to blame us rather than get rid of the politicians that kept us there.
